definitions.definition: To suffer pain ; to be the source of, or be in, pain, especially continued dull pain; to be distressed.
examples: My feet were aching for days after the marathon.
Every muscle in his body ached .

definitions.definition: To cause someone or something to suffer pain.

main_definition: ( intransitive , stative ) To suffer pain ; to be the source of, or be in, pain, especially continued dull pain; to be distressed.
secondary_definitions: ( transitive , literary , rare ) To cause someone or something to suffer pain.
